video.title: Portlandia
video.synopsis: Fred Armisen and Carrie Brownstein send up the residents of Portland, Ore. Typical targets include artisanal light bulbs and feminist bookstores.

episodes.synopsis: A bohemian couple goes to great lengths to make sure that their restaurant order is ethical and humane.
episodes.title: Farm

episodes.synopsis: Fred and Carrie meet the Mayor of Portland, who gives them a special assignment.
episodes.title: A Song for Portland

episodes.synopsis: Fred and Carrie discover that their maid is none other than their favorite singer-songwriter Aimee Mann.
episodes.title: Aimee

episodes.synopsis: When the Mayor goes missing, Fred and Carrie begin a frantic search for him.
episodes.title: Mayor Is Missing

episodes.synopsis: All of Portlandia is swept up in the excitement of a new music and film festival.
episodes.title: Blunderbuss

episodes.synopsis: The Mayor turns to Fred and Carrie to help him put together a big-league baseball team.
episodes.title: Baseball

episodes.synopsis: Fred and Carrie learn about the art of mixology and love as they venture outside of Portland on a quest.
episodes.title: Mixologist

episodes.synopsis: Portland local Ronald D. Moore helps resolve the dilemma of a young couple that has become addicted to the TV show "Battlestar Galactica."
episodes.title: One Moore Episode

episodes.synopsis: The hippest couple in Portland hosts a cool wedding, but not cool in an obvious way... cool in a never-been-done, so cool it's not-even-cool way.
episodes.title: Cool Wedding

episodes.synopsis: Two young parents devise a plan to ensure their son's admission into Portland's most elite preschool.
episodes.title: Grover

episodes.synopsis: Fred and Carrie help the Mayor cool off a recent controversy by re-branding Portland's police department.
episodes.title: Cops Redesign

episodes.synopsis: A local band's rise to stardom is disrupted by an obsessive fan, who takes dramatic measures to prevent them from selling out.
episodes.title: Cat Nap

episodes.synopsis: Peter and Nance prove they've "still got it" with an adventure on their newly purchased motorcycles.
episodes.title: Motorcycle

episodes.synopsis: Women and Women First's 10th anniversary party is disrupted by the appearance of one of the bookstore's founding members.
episodes.title: Feminist Book Store 10th Anniversary

episodes.synopsis: Fred and Carrie launch a grassroots campaign to ensure that Portland will never host the Olympic Games.
episodes.title: No Olympics

episodes.synopsis: An entire village emerges from a line at Portland's most popular new brunch spot.
episodes.title: Brunch Village

episodes.synopsis: The wait for brunch with Fred and Carrie is even longer in this one-hour edition of Portlandia's "Brunch Village.
episodes.title: Portlandia: The Brunch Special

episodes.synopsis: Peter and Nance struggle to keep off winter weight by cutting pasta from their diets, and Candace's son visits the Women and Women First bookstore.
episodes.title: Winter in Portlandia

episodes.synopsis: Spyke and Iris join forces with a gang of former MTV stars to take back MTV from tweens. Sandra pines for a mysterious man in her meditation class.
episodes.title: Take Back MTV

episodes.synopsis: The mayor sends Fred and Carrie on a door-to-door mission in Seattle to recruit new citizens for Portland.
episodes.title: Missionaries

episodes.synopsis: Nina goes to great lengths to throw an extravagant 32nd birthday party for herself.
episodes.title: Nina's Birthday

episodes.synopsis: Concerned parents Brendan and Michelle start a band that makes kids' music. Malcolm and Kris's vegan lunch has some surprising side effects.
episodes.title: Squiggleman

episodes.synopsis: Following an environmental scandal, the mayor steps down from office and moves off the grid. Musicians compete in the Battle of the Gentle Bands.
episodes.title: Off the Grid

episodes.synopsis: Marcus and Madeline help enforce the ban on same-sex marriage. A temp worker hopes to turn her gig as interim mayor of Portland into a full-time job.
episodes.title: The Temp

episodes.synopsis: A Rube Goldberg machine is created to perform the simplest of tasks. Peter and Nance host friends at the opening of their new bed-and-breakfast.
episodes.title: Soft Opening

episodes.synopsis: The city is overrun with unconventional art projects. Fred and Carrie's relationship gets complicated when they both start dating their new roommate.
episodes.title: Alexandra

episodes.synopsis: The Rats decide to move out of their newly gentrified neighborhood in search of one with more character and littering.
episodes.title: No-Fo-O-Fo-Bridge

episodes.synopsis: The entire city of Portland is in crisis after the electricity is shut off due to unpaid bills at the mayor's office.
episodes.title: Blackout

episodes.synopsis: A young woman is haunted by very informed ghosts. Doug and Claire make a big commitment to each other. Kath and Dave make the most of 15 minutes.
episodes.title: Sharing Finances

episodes.synopsis: Ecoterrorists protest animal testing at a makeup company. Bryce and Lisa Rent It Out! Toni and Candace have a car wash. Fred misses hip-hop.
episodes.title: Ecoterrorists

episodes.synopsis: A celery salesman goes to great lengths to get celery back on the table. The Order Grill is open for lunch. Carrie declares social bankruptcy.
episodes.title: Celery

episodes.synopsis: A punk from the 1980s wakes up from a coma. Nina has surprising news for Lance. Malcolm and Kris tailgate at a "Prairie Home Companion" live show.
episodes.title: Pull-Out King

episodes.synopsis: Peter drives Nance to the emergency room. Spyke gets a car. Ghavin has some questions for a singer whose band is touring through Portland.
episodes.title: Spyke Drives

episodes.synopsis: Carrie and Fred go home after a concert. Peter is reunited with his old band, the Bahama Knights -- and his ex-wife lead singer.
episodes.title: Bahama Knights

episodes.synopsis: Toni and Candace coach the Portland Trail Blazers dance team. Kickstarter videos compete at the Can'ts Film Festival. Joaquin makes a smoothie.
episodes.title: Trail Blazers

episodes.synopsis: Brendan and Michelle decide that it's finally time to try drugs. Carrie's brother comes to visit. Women and Women First is visited by the cops.
episodes.title: Late in Life Drug Use

episodes.synopsis: Mr. Mayor unveils Portland's official 3-D printer. A minister reminds us that church is an option. Art students make anti-corporate paintings.
episodes.title: 3D Printer

episodes.synopsis: Portlandia gets away for the weekend to New Beavertown, Oregon. Toni and Candace lead a feminist moon retreat for women.
episodes.title: Getting Away
